tridb_graph_vid_cache.patch — advisor plan 034 / DEV-1345 (PERF-03): point the TJS operator's
graph reachable-set resolution at the backend-local CACHED reverse translator.

graphReachableT (tjs_operator.cpp) now SPI-probes graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext_cached(%lld)
instead of graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext(%lld). The cached function (repo-owned
src/graph_store/graph_am.c + graph_store_am--0.1.0.sql) is byte-identical to the shim but
reverse-translates each neighbor vid -> ext_id through a session-lifetime hash (~50ns) instead
of a correlated btree + SPI subquery (~1us/neighbor, ~2ms at fanout 2000). SPI shape, probe-ONCE-
at-Open caching, and the single-connection nesting discipline (DEV-1236) are unchanged — only the
translator behind the probe changes.

Applies LAST in the chain, after tridb_graph_v1_rewire.patch (advisor plan 025), whose
graph_store.gph_neighbors_ext probe string this rewrites.

Test: test/graph_vid_cache_test.sql (cached == uncached parity + relcache-invalidation hook fires).
Sentinel: gph_neighbors_ext_cached in src/tjs_operator.cpp.
